<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910924-0043</DOCNO><DOCID>910924-0043.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- BSN Corp.:   All American/Maxpro Line   Is Sold to Riddell Sports</HL><DATE>09/24/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C25</SO><CO>   BSN RIDL</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY (REC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>RESTRUCTURINGS, RECAPITALIZATION (RCN)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   BSN Corp. said it sold its All American/Maxpro division toRiddell Sports Inc. for $17 million in Riddell stock, equalto a 27% stake in the maker of football helmets and otherprotective equipment.   BSN said that Riddell, based in Chicago, also assumed $3million of debt. BSN said it retained about $16 million inMaxpro receivables that it expects to collect within 60 days.</LP><TEXT>   Maxpro makes and distributes protective sports equipment.   BSN, based in Dallas, said the sale is part of an assetrestructuring program under which it has sold assets and spunoff a unit. BSN now owns a maker of trophies and awards and a27% stake in both Riddell and Sports Supply Group Inc. BSNsaid it plans to periodically review other alternatives toimprove its share price, including beginning a cash or stockdividend and repurchasing its stock or debt.   In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,BSN rose 25 cents to $6.875.</TEXT></DOC>